  "text_preview": "\"work\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► WORK: The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for: work / labor / employment (and related concepts) The sign for \"work\" is made by shaping both hands into \"fist shapes\" (the letter \"s.\") With your palms facing downward, use your dominant fist to tap the wrist or the side of your non-dominant fist a few times. WORK: Memory Aid: Think of working with a hammer. While the sign \"WORK\" can (in context) be used to mean \"job\" -- there is a more common way of signing \"job.\" See: JOB The word \"work\" has meanings other than just \"perform labor.\" If you use work in sentences such as: \"That worked!\" or \"That works!\" or \"It didn't work!\" -- what you really mean is \"success,\" \"succeed,\" or \"satisfies a need.\" If y"
